1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:08,140 --> 00:00:08,620
What's up?

3
00:00:08,620 --> 00:00:11,600
Didn't you say you were going to Kneifl's for goulash with six dumplings?

4
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,400
The goulash ran out.

5
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:13,680
I only got the six dumplings.

6
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:14,750
And this?

7
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:17,050
That's dessert.

8
00:00:17,330 --> 00:00:17,810
Relax.

9
00:00:17,810 --> 00:00:19,110
You know how much Lexa eats?

10
00:00:19,310 --> 00:00:20,590
Lexa is still growing.

11
00:00:20,590 --> 00:00:21,170
Ozzak isn't.

12
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:24,030
You can't stop growth, buddy.

13
00:00:24,030 --> 00:00:25,070
How come you're not at the pub?

14
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:27,950
You know why I feel guilty?

15
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:30,750
I'd rather not.

16
00:00:30,850 --> 00:00:32,250
That's actually why I'm here.

17
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:34,950
I need a ride to Celadna for the brewery trade fair.

18
00:00:35,070 --> 00:00:36,090
It's just overnight.

19
00:00:36,370 --> 00:00:37,590
To buy a new tap.

20
00:00:38,450 --> 00:00:39,790
I was thirsty.

21
00:00:39,950 --> 00:00:42,190
And why can't someone else drive?

22
00:00:42,450 --> 00:00:48,050
Well normally my boss drives me, but last time I was going through a rough patch and it turned into a wild night.

23
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:51,950
I got drunk and mistook him for my ex.

24
00:00:53,050 --> 00:00:57,450
So something happened between you two?

25
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:58,880
You could say that.

26
00:00:59,460 --> 00:01:01,020
And he doesn't want a repeat?

27
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:04,220
Well you know, nobody enjoys being held by the tie and beaten with a table leg.

28
00:01:05,500 --> 00:01:07,040
Look, this doesn't really work for me.

29
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:08,260
And I'm already over it.

30
00:01:08,460 --> 00:01:11,240
But I have the shop to look after and who's gonna watch Iva?

31
00:01:11,490 --> 00:01:12,250
What do you mean watch?

32
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:13,970
Nobody watches Sasa and Lexa either.

33
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:16,650
Oh right, the kids actually.

34
00:01:17,550 --> 00:01:19,260
So should I ask the building manager again?

35
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:20,640
She's been dead for two years.

36
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:21,380
Really?

37
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:25,300
So nobody's been watching them for two years.

38
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:26,120
You should go.

39
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:28,750
It's your duty to us thirsty folk.

40
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:31,850
Maybe they'll even have that new high-flow tap there.

41
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:33,760
I'm having problems with the accountant right now.

42
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,640
She's nervous because she can't calculate the VAT.

43
00:01:36,040 --> 00:01:38,400
All of May is written on beer coasters.

44
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,060
Bro, you have to go.

45
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:41,800
We'll manage here without you.

46
00:01:42,110 --> 00:01:43,150
And you'll watch the kids?

47
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:46,030
If Iva, Sasa and Lexa help me out?

48
00:01:46,030 --> 00:01:46,910
No problem.

49
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:51,250
But there is a problem.

50
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:52,550
A big problem.

51
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:55,550
Where do I go for drinks tonight when the Badger is closed?

52
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:58,240
I set you up at the Turkey, they're expecting you.

53
00:01:58,240 --> 00:01:59,560
They bought an extra keg of beer.

54
00:02:00,850 --> 00:02:01,450
That would work.

55
00:02:02,090 --> 00:02:02,530
Yeah.

56
00:02:03,550 --> 00:02:04,820
And watch out for Sasa.

57
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,350
Make sure she's not drinking.

58
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:08,350
And that was a joke.

59
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:41,950
I had to take care of something.

60
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:46,460
Marcelka, why on earth are you dragging a fish to work?

61
00:02:46,460 --> 00:02:47,440
It's Zoran's cudla.

62
00:02:47,850 --> 00:02:49,760
It's so cuddly-looking.

63
00:02:50,050 --> 00:02:52,640
Cudla means young and beautiful in Croatian.

64
00:02:52,850 --> 00:02:56,080
I bought it for Zoran so he'd think of me every time he sees it.

65
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,800
You should have bought him an old piranha instead.

66
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,340
I took her to the vet.

67
00:03:01,460 --> 00:03:03,160
She's showing signs of fish tuberculosis.

68
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:07,960
Marcelka, I have to leave unexpectedly, so you'll have to handle the accountant yourself.

69
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:13,650
Well, Ozzak found the rest of the March accounting.

70
00:03:13,850 --> 00:03:15,250
In the Sports section?

71
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:17,950
Well, some in the supplements and crosswords too.

72
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,840
Tomas, but today doesn't work for me.

73
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,220
I have to watch the cudla.

74
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:23,620
Well then, take her to the accountant with you.

75
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:24,980
She needs to be calm.

76
00:03:25,020 --> 00:03:26,960
She mustn't be put in any stressful situation.

77
00:03:27,260 --> 00:03:27,860
The accountant?

78
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,000
No, the fish.

79
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:31,550
Ozzak can go to the accountant.

80
00:03:35,950 --> 00:03:39,130
Well, the accountant also mustn't be put in any stressful situation.

81
00:03:39,650 --> 00:03:41,150
And someone has to go.

82
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:43,130
Ozzak can watch it too.

83
00:03:43,130 --> 00:03:45,350
He's watching the kids, so he can watch the fish.

84
00:03:46,150 --> 00:03:47,650
You're watching the kids?

85
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:48,850
Sure.

86
00:03:50,150 --> 00:03:51,150
Alright then.

87
00:03:51,750 --> 00:03:54,150
But Zoran would kill himself if anything happened to her.

88
00:03:54,650 --> 00:03:56,450
Actually, he'd rather kill someone else.

89
00:03:57,650 --> 00:03:58,950
Here's the food.

90
00:03:59,330 --> 00:04:01,590
And if anything happens, call right away.

91
00:04:01,590 --> 00:04:05,950
Oh, and for the worst case, here's the number for Fish in Distress.

92
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:08,450
Put it in the back.

93
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:10,210
If it has tuberculosis, I don't want to catch it.

94
00:04:10,590 --> 00:04:11,070
That's impossible.

95
00:04:11,130 --> 00:04:12,090
It has to be in the light.

96
00:04:13,110 --> 00:04:14,050
Fine then.

97
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:15,710
But one cough and it's out.

98
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:20,250
So where are you going?

99
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:22,810
What's up?

100
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:25,250
We're going to the tap trade fair.

101
00:04:25,750 --> 00:04:27,930
And is this like a uniform?

102
00:04:28,150 --> 00:04:30,470
I need a discount, I won't get one in sweatpants.

103
00:04:30,470 --> 00:04:32,270
Well then let's go.

104
00:04:35,150 --> 00:04:35,730
See ya.

105
00:04:35,850 --> 00:04:38,590
Lexa, no trouble.

106
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:39,950
And you, Sasa, same goes for you.

107
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:45,200
Thank you, Marcelka.

108
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,800
And Ozzak, don't forget.

109
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:48,650
You have responsibility.

110
00:04:56,650 --> 00:04:58,450
I'm leaving her with you reluctantly.

111
00:04:58,950 --> 00:05:02,050
If anything happens to her, you know what's coming.

112
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,900
Relax, we'll get along fine.

113
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:04,440
Alright.

114
00:05:05,550 --> 00:05:06,380
At least she doesn't talk.

115
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:07,900
Unlike some people.

116
00:05:09,450 --> 00:05:11,250
Well, where are you?

117
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,200
Parents are out, it's party time.

118
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,020
Yay!

119
00:05:20,020 --> 00:05:20,160
Yeah!

120
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:22,560
Now hold on, hold on, let's get this straight.

121
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,560
It won't be totally free.

122
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,640
But uncle.

123
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:30,260
Look, your parents gave me the responsibility.

124
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:32,350
Unfortunately, I have to establish a strict regime.

125
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:37,820
At exactly 16:00 you will bring me hot water for grog, I have the mug and rum here.

126
00:05:38,150 --> 00:05:39,350
It's a long day, clear?

127
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:39,840
Clear.

128
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:43,100
At exactly 18:00 I close up and head to the Turkey.

129
00:05:43,140 --> 00:05:49,180
You can come with me, but at 10 PM, that's 22:00, you must be home because your bro will be calling.

130
00:05:49,300 --> 00:05:55,060
Then you have free time, but at exactly 1 AM you have to come pick me up at the Turkey and drive me home.

131
00:05:55,140 --> 00:05:55,640
Clear?

132
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:56,440
Clear.

133
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:59,700
Wow, I'll be walking Mr. Ozzak home from the pub.

134
00:05:59,950 --> 00:06:01,940
That's my second biggest dream.

135
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:03,020
The first one is.

136
00:06:03,020 --> 00:06:04,850
Forget about that one, Lexa.

137
00:06:07,350 --> 00:06:08,650
We have a free apartment.

138
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:09,910
A free evening.

139
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:11,530
We have to make the most of it.

140
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:12,810
Do something rebellious.

141
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:15,350
Sure, let's not brush our teeth.

142
00:06:15,350 --> 00:06:19,350
That would make you, Lexa, the world's greatest rebel, but that's not what I meant.

143
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,350
We can do whatever we want.

144
00:06:23,840 --> 00:06:24,980
I can't think of anything.

145
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:29,360
Come on, something adventurous, something we've never experienced before.

146
00:06:29,650 --> 00:06:30,300
I know.

147
00:06:30,650 --> 00:06:33,750
We can stay up all night and read The Count of Monte Cristo.

148
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:35,600
You know what?

149
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,350
Let's get some ideas.

150
00:06:39,550 --> 00:06:42,950
Maybe something from the advanced chapter.

151
00:06:43,650 --> 00:06:45,210
Find a taxi in Zizkov.

152
00:06:45,450 --> 00:06:48,350
Or get from the main train station to the tram without injury.

153
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:50,150
Yeah, that's a challenge.

154
00:06:50,650 --> 00:06:51,800
Isn't it dangerous?

155
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,950
Well yeah, but that's the whole point.

156
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:57,390
You know what, just pick something yourself.

157
00:06:57,690 --> 00:06:59,750
Okay, something less dangerous.

158
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:01,950
This one's funny.

159
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:05,250
Go to dinner at a Chinese restaurant with your boss's dog.

160
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:06,750
We don't have a boss.

161
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:09,550
Score some gingerbread at Karlovo namesti.

162
00:07:09,950 --> 00:07:11,250
What's hard about that?

163
00:07:12,220 --> 00:07:12,700
Let me see.

164
00:07:14,350 --> 00:07:17,550
Yeah but you're looking at the suicide category.

165
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:19,550
We need more like beginner stuff.

166
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:23,780
And here look, hit every pub in Letna and have a mojito in each one.

167
00:07:24,050 --> 00:07:25,950
Or ski down Petrin on cross-country skis, or swim across the Vltava.

168
00:07:27,460 --> 00:07:29,300
No way, it's terribly dirty.

169
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:34,960
Here's something, male strip show, that could be awesome.

170
00:07:35,250 --> 00:07:37,250
No way, there could be naked guys there.

171
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:39,950
Sasa, you'll see it'll be fun.

172
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:42,370
Hey.

173
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,850
So what are you planning since we're free?

174
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:45,470
A strip show.

175
00:07:46,670 --> 00:07:47,270
Awesome!

176
00:07:50,050 --> 00:07:51,770
But we're going to a strip show.

177
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:52,610
A male one.

178
00:07:53,150 --> 00:07:53,750
Awesome!

179
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:58,650
We'd love to have you along, but only women are allowed in.

180
00:07:59,260 --> 00:08:00,080
No way.

181
00:08:00,420 --> 00:08:02,300
I want to go.

182
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:04,950
You can swim across the Vltava.

183
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:14,050
Mr. Ozzak, I have to tell you something.

184
00:08:14,550 --> 00:08:16,950
The girls want to secretly go to a male strip show.

185
00:08:17,550 --> 00:08:18,540
Well, great.

186
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,080
Go find something to do yourself, kid.

187
00:08:20,140 --> 00:08:20,400
Go.

188
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:23,650
But they won't take me along.

189
00:08:24,450 --> 00:08:26,080
Well, that's a pretty wise decision.

190
00:08:26,350 --> 00:08:28,350
They probably figure you wouldn't enjoy it.

191
00:08:31,150 --> 00:08:33,450
Did you glue the fish to those bottles on purpose?

192
00:08:33,490 --> 00:08:33,970
What?

193
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:42,950
It's not breathing.

194
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:46,050
Let me look, kid.

195
00:08:46,050 --> 00:08:47,750
Take a good look at this fish.

196
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:48,300
Why?

197
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,980
So you can buy one that looks really similar.

198
00:08:52,450 --> 00:08:53,450
Now go.

199
00:09:01,370 --> 00:09:01,850
A fish.

200
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,620
Hey, look who showed up.

201
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:15,620
Pipa, you gorgeous thing, great to see you.

202
00:09:15,880 --> 00:09:16,760
Hey, Milda.

203
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:18,140
Haven't they locked you up yet?

204
00:09:21,850 --> 00:09:23,050
The guys were already asking if you'd show up.

205
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,230
You know, it wouldn't be the same without you.

206
00:09:25,310 --> 00:09:28,990
You bet it wouldn't, but I'm here, so tonight we're going to tear it up.

207
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:30,450
Sure thing, the samples have already arrived.

208
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:36,310
Check it out, Hustan, Golden Beaver, Vorar, the beer, even international participation, some Swedes from Pivson.

209
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:42,050
So this is your Libor.

210
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:44,330
No, I'm definitely not.

211
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:53,250
Relax, relax, you must be one tough dude, because snagging this tap here is like diving with sharks with a bloody steak in your crotch.

212
00:09:54,850 --> 00:10:04,280
Wait, I'm just the ride, I've never even thought about it, but now we're friends.

213
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,720
Well, after all, we're also here for the kids, right?

214
00:10:07,220 --> 00:10:08,740
What do I hear, what do I hear?

215
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,180
Pipa, you've got some little ones?

216
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:13,140
Well yeah, there'll be one or two.

217
00:10:13,150 --> 00:10:15,850
But they're already practicing leaving the nest by jumping off the roof.

218
00:10:17,110 --> 00:10:19,630
Excuse me, could we get our rooms?

219
00:10:20,090 --> 00:10:21,730
Rooms, rooms, right?

220
00:10:21,730 --> 00:10:27,590
Easy for you to say, rooms, but I've only got one room prepared for you, because we're in a bit of a renovation here, you know?

221
00:10:29,610 --> 00:10:32,650
But looking at you two, it probably won't bother you anyway, right?

222
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,080
Hold on a moment.

223
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:38,140
I demand my room that I had reserved.

224
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:40,840
I have a right to it and I'm not moving until I get the keys.

225
00:10:41,750 --> 00:10:42,640
Let's go then.

226
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:43,880
Sir, just a little...

227
00:10:44,550 --> 00:10:45,550
A bit nervous, huh?

228
00:10:46,110 --> 00:10:48,530
Whatever, fine, two rooms it is, as you wish.

229
00:10:48,830 --> 00:10:49,170
There you go.

230
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,550
Satisfied.

231
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:55,050
Have a pleasant stay.

232
00:10:57,450 --> 00:10:59,720
We're still missing one invoice from August.

233
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:01,850
We need to find it, I'll be back in a moment.

234
00:11:02,610 --> 00:11:03,090
Hold on.

235
00:11:04,050 --> 00:11:04,950
Where's the cudla?

236
00:11:06,050 --> 00:11:09,270
She was dozing off so I put her next door in the dark to have some peace.

237
00:11:09,270 --> 00:11:19,240
You can't do that.

238
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:22,130
When she's in the dark, she always plays dead.

239
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:25,550
Well, as soon as you put her in the light, she'll be fine again.

240
00:11:28,850 --> 00:11:30,950
Sometimes it takes her up to half an hour though.

241
00:11:33,550 --> 00:11:35,910
Zoran is so happy she's okay now.

242
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:38,810
He says he can't wait to see her again.

243
00:11:38,910 --> 00:11:40,470
You know, his darling.

244
00:11:43,840 --> 00:11:44,380
Hello.

245
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:45,800
Hi.

246
00:11:46,350 --> 00:11:49,350
You fell asleep on us.

247
00:11:54,550 --> 00:11:57,650
Well, see, what did I tell you.

248
00:11:57,700 --> 00:12:00,100
We also know everything about fish in our family.

249
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:01,940
My cousin is even an ichthyologist.

250
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,900
That's news.

251
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:06,150
Your whole family are ichthyologists.

252
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:08,550
The worse thing is I can't find that invoice.

253
00:12:08,550 --> 00:12:10,750
Any idea where it could be?

254
00:12:13,350 --> 00:12:16,070
This, but it's so shiny I can't read it.

255
00:12:16,070 --> 00:12:18,060
What is it?

256
00:12:18,060 --> 00:12:20,980
Well for an ichthyologist, you don't know much about fish.

257
00:12:20,980 --> 00:12:21,580
Mackerel, right?

258
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:23,380
Ah.

259
00:12:24,750 --> 00:12:25,080
Well...

260
00:12:25,650 --> 00:12:28,850
I'm off then.

261
00:12:29,550 --> 00:12:32,460
This is going to take a while to explain to her.

262
00:12:32,750 --> 00:12:34,980
The poor thing is nervous.

263
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:40,550
And stop hiding the cudla.

264
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:50,890
I didn't have any money, so the manager kept my shoes as collateral.

265
00:12:50,890 --> 00:12:52,930
She wanted my hat, but I talked her out of it.

266
00:12:52,930 --> 00:12:57,030
In that case, Lexa, you're a hero and you deserve those 50 crowns.

267
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:04,680
Is the aquarium over there?

268
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:05,080
Yeah.

269
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:06,640
So what are you waiting for, Lexa?

270
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:24,410
16:00 hours.

271
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:31,550
Ivuska, you're such a sweetheart.

272
00:13:43,650 --> 00:13:44,390
Let's go.

273
00:13:46,650 --> 00:13:47,650
We have until ten.

274
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:49,380
Sasa, what's wrong?

275
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,040
I'm scared.

276
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:52,460
Jesus, of what?

277
00:13:53,650 --> 00:13:54,450
Everything.

278
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:57,450
We don't have to try everything I said.

279
00:13:58,950 --> 00:13:59,950
And what do we skip?

280
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:01,850
How about the strip show.

281
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:03,720
You promise?

282
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,400
Sure.

283
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:07,140
We'll just do the mojito and save the strip show for next time.

284
00:14:07,550 --> 00:14:09,550
Can I bring The Count of Monte Cristo?

285
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:10,780
Absolutely.

286
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:16,150
Let's go then.

287
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:23,250
It's all scales.

288
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,350
You don't have a fish?

289
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,750
I thought just the aquarium would be enough.

290
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,500
Lexa, for God's sake, it goes without saying you need a fish.

291
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,600
You buy it automatically.

292
00:14:37,980 --> 00:14:38,500
Got it?

293
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:39,320
Yeah.

294
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:50,220
Hello.

295
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:58,740
Front desk?

296
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:01,350
Excuse me, there's a handyman in my room.

297
00:15:02,350 --> 00:15:03,850
What renovation?

298
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:04,600
Yes!

299
00:15:08,450 --> 00:15:10,850
Excuse me, this bathroom doesn't work?

300
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:13,910
Nope, this is the only bathroom that's perfectly fine.

301
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:15,170
You know, the renovation.

302
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:19,650
Yeah boss, the green towel is ours and the red one is the roofer's.

303
00:15:19,950 --> 00:15:21,150
Just make sure he behaves.

304
00:15:21,950 --> 00:15:23,280
Better not share toothbrushes either.

305
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:24,360
In your own interest.

306
00:15:25,750 --> 00:15:28,020
What do you mean toothbrushes?

307
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:29,940
What do you mean your towel?

308
00:15:29,940 --> 00:15:30,980
Just ours?

309
00:15:31,220 --> 00:15:33,000
What kind of questions are those?

310
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,160
City folk.

311
00:15:35,110 --> 00:15:35,670
Right.

312
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:36,150
Right.

313
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:39,120
Did you see that?

314
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:39,460
Yeah.

315
00:15:40,350 --> 00:15:42,160
You ready for a proper bender?

316
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:45,400
Once we finish shopping, we'll party like the good old days.

317
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:51,230
It's just cold.

318
00:15:53,850 --> 00:15:55,250
It's almost done now.

319
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:03,510
We're just missing the receipt from that big trash metal delivery you made behind our backs.

320
00:16:03,510 --> 00:16:04,330
Do you really want it?

321
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:10,450
But you have to give it back.

322
00:16:14,350 --> 00:16:17,150
I smell something like someone's been cooking fish.

323
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:21,250
Ozzak, where's the cudla?

324
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:30,550
I wanted to point out that you're keeping her in a round aquarium.

325
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,980
It makes her dizzy and then she feels nauseous.

326
00:16:33,140 --> 00:16:34,880
As an ichthyologist you should know that.

327
00:16:36,060 --> 00:16:37,600
A pub shouldn't be round either.

328
00:16:37,820 --> 00:16:39,960
I always get the worst hangover when I drink at the Rotunda.

329
00:16:41,580 --> 00:16:43,640
Oh, and it's also shatterproof.

330
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:48,350
You wouldn't believe how easily a terrible accident can happen.

331
00:16:50,750 --> 00:16:52,350
Well, Ozzak, I'd never have believed how beautifully you'd take care of the cudla.

332
00:16:56,090 --> 00:16:57,650
But I still need to deliver that invoice.

333
00:16:57,770 --> 00:16:59,330
Could you watch her a little longer?

334
00:17:00,050 --> 00:17:00,650
Well, wait, but I'm already watching the kids.

335
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:02,930
Right, Lexa?

336
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:04,130
Yep.

337
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:06,070
That would be too much for me.

338
00:17:06,270 --> 00:17:08,150
And besides, rules are rules.

339
00:17:08,310 --> 00:17:10,970
Sure, at 18:00 sharp, off to the Turkey.

340
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:12,410
You'll manage for sure.

341
00:17:16,950 --> 00:17:19,150
Please, Mr. Ozzak, Zoran and I will be grateful.

342
00:17:19,650 --> 00:17:22,710
Fine, if you'll leave and stop talking, then maybe.

343
00:17:22,710 --> 00:17:23,050
Thanks.

344
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:30,280
Mr. Ozzak, I need to buy back my stuff.

345
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:30,720
Right.

346
00:17:36,150 --> 00:17:37,470
I won't make the same mistake again.

347
00:17:42,160 --> 00:17:42,680
Yeah.

348
00:17:46,550 --> 00:17:47,420
There's nothing there, kid.

349
00:17:47,420 --> 00:17:56,740
While you're there, grab more fish.

350
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:04,850
Ozzak?

351
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:07,350
How come you're not at the pub?

352
00:18:07,430 --> 00:18:08,550
I just didn't feel like it.

353
00:18:09,170 --> 00:18:09,730
Didn't feel like it?

354
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:11,950
Did something happen?

355
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:13,750
Put Iva on.

356
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:15,130
Iva?

357
00:18:16,650 --> 00:18:17,950
She's in the bathroom.

358
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:20,850
Then I'll wait.

359
00:18:20,950 --> 00:18:23,490
Yeah, okay then.

360
00:18:24,050 --> 00:18:27,790
She just ran past me, bro, she ran to the basement to check the water meter, you know?

361
00:18:27,810 --> 00:18:28,650
That'll take a while.

362
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:31,610
Wanna talk to Lexa?

363
00:18:31,610 --> 00:18:34,310
I don't want to talk to Lexa, I want to talk to Iva.

364
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:37,170
To Iva.

365
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:39,360
Iva, Iva.

366
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,880
Iva, Iva, Iva.

367
00:18:41,360 --> 00:18:42,340
Iva, Iva, Iva.

368
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:43,400
Iva's here now.

369
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,260
Right away, she just ran in.

370
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,100
Dad, dad.

371
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,700
Hi, dad.

372
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,250
How are you?

373
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:51,340
I was just downstairs checking the water meter.

374
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:52,860
What did Simona say?

375
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:57,480
Well yeah, Simona did disappear somewhere, but she'll turn up again.

376
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,480
That's a shame.

377
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:00,450
Sasa just wanted to talk to her.

378
00:19:01,050 --> 00:19:02,850
Sasa, do you want to talk to my dad?

379
00:19:03,740 --> 00:19:05,200
No, she says she doesn't.

380
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:07,580
Well, hopefully Simona shows up soon.

381
00:19:09,450 --> 00:19:13,350
And Simona's here now, so everything is fine.

382
00:19:14,990 --> 00:19:15,970
Sasa is missing.

383
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:18,850
You have to help me find her, she's totally helpless on her own.

384
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:19,690
But I'm watching the fish.

385
00:19:21,250 --> 00:19:22,050
I'm naked.

386
00:19:23,150 --> 00:19:24,850
Well thanks a lot then.

387
00:19:27,650 --> 00:19:30,380
Well, let's go, everything's fine, glad to hear it.

388
00:19:30,950 --> 00:19:32,260
Same here, bye.

389
00:19:34,650 --> 00:19:36,250
You really pissed me off, Libor.

390
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:48,050
What do we do with the rest of them?

391
00:19:48,950 --> 00:19:50,050
We have to get rid of them.

392
00:19:55,850 --> 00:19:57,350
So what are you waiting for?

393
00:19:58,950 --> 00:20:00,150
You turn it on.

394
00:20:01,250 --> 00:20:04,290
So you want to listen to death metal, huh?

395
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:06,450
I see you're still soft.

396
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:12,050
What is it, Mr. Ozzak?

397
00:20:12,450 --> 00:20:13,550
It's bad, Lexa.

398
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:15,550
We've got seven left.

399
00:20:16,430 --> 00:20:17,210
Now what?

400
00:20:20,950 --> 00:20:22,250
I'm finally here.

401
00:20:24,050 --> 00:20:25,450
What are you standing around for?

402
00:20:26,150 --> 00:20:27,450
We can't turn on the blender.

403
00:20:28,950 --> 00:20:29,950
It's broken.

404
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:33,060
There we go.

405
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,850
Well, we're going to need this.

406
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,700
Come on, go lie down, Simona, come on.

407
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:46,820
But I don't want to.

408
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,940
Go to your room, go, go, come on.

409
00:21:06,190 --> 00:21:07,600
Who are you?

410
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,580
I'm a locksmith.

411
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:11,120
And what are you doing here?

412
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:13,450
You know, renovation.

413
00:21:14,050 --> 00:21:15,750
Get out, out.

414
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:18,450
You can't sleep here anyway.

415
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:28,090
You have to let me in even after closing, today is Thursday and you know what happens on Thursday, you know.

416
00:21:28,090 --> 00:21:29,250
Fine, steam it is then.

417
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:43,550
How did you get in here?

418
00:21:43,950 --> 00:21:46,050
I'm a locksmith, are you deaf?

419
00:21:47,860 --> 00:21:48,420
Libor?

420
00:21:52,250 --> 00:21:53,180
Don't you know how to knock?

421
00:21:53,550 --> 00:21:54,650
Sorry, excuse me.

422
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:01,950
Simonka is waiting.

423
00:22:04,650 --> 00:22:06,940
It's a miracle how much she's improved since this morning.

424
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:10,340
She's so chill now, like it's not even her.

425
00:22:10,340 --> 00:22:10,780
But it is.

426
00:22:14,050 --> 00:22:21,540
I drank the rum and swam in the Vltava, which is two adventures right there and totally chill.

427
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:23,600
It wasn't all that chill though, was it?

428
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,780
True, I lost the book.

429
00:22:25,940 --> 00:22:29,060
But then I went to Karlak and was looking for gingerbread.

430
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:32,980
But the guy didn't have it ready, so he just gave me baking powder.

431
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,660
And then we played tag.

432
00:22:37,320 --> 00:22:39,460
And it was a real adventure.

433
00:22:39,950 --> 00:22:41,140
You should go to bed.

434
00:22:41,140 --> 00:22:42,680
And now to the strip show!

435
00:22:44,950 --> 00:22:45,800
Can I come with you?

436
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:47,250
You're already naked.

437
00:22:47,650 --> 00:22:49,750
Uncle, say something.

438
00:22:50,050 --> 00:22:51,770
Fine, go ahead.

439
00:22:51,770 --> 00:22:53,510
But Lexa, make sure you put something on.

440
00:22:53,710 --> 00:22:55,470
And for Sasa, just zipping up her jacket should be enough.

441
00:22:56,670 --> 00:22:57,970
I'd better go then.

442
00:23:09,750 --> 00:23:12,750
Well, I can see everything's fine, so I'm heading to the Turkey.

443
00:23:15,950 --> 00:23:21,250
And unfortunately the schedule's been pushed back because we're running late, so come get me at 8 AM, clear?

444
00:23:21,250 --> 00:23:21,810
Sure.

445
00:23:31,150 --> 00:23:32,830
How could you do this to me, Libor.

446
00:23:33,590 --> 00:23:34,610
I'm not Libor.

447
00:23:34,750 --> 00:23:36,030
But you always say that.

448
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:37,790
Because it's true, I'm Tomas.

449
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:41,850
I've always known you're Tomas, why are you telling me?

450
00:23:41,850 --> 00:23:43,630
Thank God, I was starting to think you'd lost your mind.

451
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:48,660
Did you think it's easy to just chat normally with you after everything?

452
00:23:48,660 --> 00:23:49,800
After what?

453
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:53,950
You left me alone with the kids and then show up like nothing happened.

454
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,840
Something did happen, Libor, it did.

455
00:23:56,460 --> 00:23:57,700
I'm not Libor, Simona.

456
00:23:58,050 --> 00:24:00,240
That's no excuse.

457
00:24:00,240 --> 00:24:01,900
Look, just go lie down in your room, okay?

458
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:02,780
Don't make a scene, go, go.

459
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,060
I'm perfectly fine.

460
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:07,350
Where are we?

461
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:10,850
And where are the kids?

462
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:13,250
The kids are at home with Ozzak.

463
00:24:13,450 --> 00:24:14,610
My brother.

464
00:24:14,750 --> 00:24:17,390
Well, then I'm not worried if they're with your brother.

465
00:24:17,650 --> 00:24:18,650
I am though.

466
00:24:19,580 --> 00:24:19,940
Right.

467
00:24:21,150 --> 00:24:24,550
Maybe we shouldn't have left them alone with Ozzak, you know, Tomas?

468
00:24:26,150 --> 00:24:28,450
They'll manage, the kids are resourceful.

469
00:24:29,050 --> 00:24:30,750
Just tell me, what's going to happen with us?

470
00:24:31,050 --> 00:24:32,750
Are you going to leave me again?

471
00:24:33,050 --> 00:24:34,450
What do you mean, what's going to happen with us?

472
00:24:35,150 --> 00:24:37,070
You're my husband, Libor.

473
00:24:37,450 --> 00:24:39,150
Don't forget that.

474
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:42,550
I'm not Libor.

475
00:24:48,450 --> 00:24:49,750
You don't know anything.

476
00:24:50,550 --> 00:24:52,750
But the kids are yours, Tomas.

477
00:24:56,150 --> 00:24:56,650
Not Libor's.

478
00:24:58,230 --> 00:24:59,470
Did you mean to say Libor's?

479
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:10,750
And the April accounting is all sorted too.

480
00:25:14,650 --> 00:25:15,650
Dad, are you okay?

481
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:20,270
Yeah, it was a bit wild there, you know, the renovation.

482
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:21,910
Simona went straight to bed.

483
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:24,950
And how about you guys, how did you manage?

484
00:25:26,350 --> 00:25:28,450
Nothing happened at all.

485
00:25:29,350 --> 00:25:33,150
Nobody went swimming, nobody bought drugs, nobody got wasted.

486
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:34,700
Except me.

487
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:36,600
Boring, it was boring here.

488
00:25:36,820 --> 00:25:37,300
Exactly.

489
00:25:37,460 --> 00:25:39,060
Well, that's what I like to hear.

490
00:25:41,950 --> 00:25:44,450
It must have been quite a scene in Celadna though.

491
00:25:44,950 --> 00:25:45,750
And why do you think?

492
00:25:45,950 --> 00:25:47,270
Mom fell asleep leaning against the door frame.

493
00:25:47,550 --> 00:25:50,450
That happened all the time when dad was around.

494
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:53,720
Tomas, you're back already?

495
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:55,350
Did you enjoy the trip?

496
00:25:55,650 --> 00:25:58,510
I must say, you took wonderful care of the cudla.

497
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:01,780
Maybe it's the new aquarium, or something, she's so lively now.

498
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,320
Or maybe it's the new food.

499
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:08,860
The cudla was so frisky she bit little Lupinek here.

500
00:26:09,250 --> 00:26:11,650
I can't keep them together anymore.

501
00:26:11,850 --> 00:26:14,050
Could you watch him for me, Mr. Ozzak?

502
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:16,690
We're going to need a bigger blender.

503
00:26:22,650 --> 00:26:24,350
Sasa, you look like you've been scrubbed.

504
00:26:25,050 --> 00:26:26,480
Have you been drinking?

505
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:30,360
That was a joke.

506
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:44,190
And where's the third one?

507
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:55,450
What are you saying?

508
00:26:57,650 --> 00:26:58,570
It's alive.

509
00:26:59,250 --> 00:27:01,050
It's alive.

510
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:02,480
For now.
